The National Working Committee (NWC) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), on behalf of the National Executive Committee (NEC), on Friday, said it has approved the dissolution of the State Caretaker Committee for the Cross River state chapter of the party This was contained in a statement by Kola Ologbondiyan National Publicity Secretary of the party. According to the statement, “The decision is in pursuant to the powers conferred on the NWC by the PDP Constitution. “Consequently, the NWC has constituted a new State Caretaker Committee to pilot the affairs of the chapter of the party at the state level” “The members of the new State Caretaker Committee for Cross River state are as follows: Barr. Efiok Cobham (Chairman) Barr. Attah Ochinke Dr. Uke Enun Prof. Walter Mboto Hon. Rita Ayim (Publicity Secretary) Hon. Mike Usibe Hon. Christopher Ekpo Mr. Victor Effiom Okon Prince K.J. Agba Hon. Eko Atu (Secretary) “All other structures of the party at the local government and ward levels in the state remain intact,” the statement said. Buhari: Goodluck Jonathan’s media office reports Fr Mbaka to Pope Francis 